          "settings": {
            "heading": "",
            "text": "<p>Every now and then, parents across the UAE look for things that let kids learn, have fun, yet stick to healthier choices. From learning-focused playthings to fun ways to draw and color. These choices help little ones grow while keeping smiles healthy. Some picks teach through play. Others make brushing feel like part of the day’s adventure. Each item fits real routines. So does strong hygiene when the right tools are on hand.<br/>Looking after little ones gets easier when playtime teaches something new. Toys that invite coloring spark imagination just as much as they build focus. A two year old might start learning through stacking shapes or sorting colors. Five year olds often enjoy challenges that mix fun with problem solving. Brushing teeth turns into a habit kids accept when games are part of the routine. Learning feels natural when it hides inside playful moments.<br/></p>",
